<http://www.oie.int/messages/alertemng.htm>

FOOT AND MOUTH DISEASE (VIRUS TYPE O) IN MONGOLIA
-------------------------------------------------
Information received on 21 Jul 2002 from Dr Ravdan Sanjaatogtokh,
Director, State Veterinary Services, Ministry of Food and
Agriculture, Ulaanbaatar:
Report date: 21 Jul 2002.
Nature of diagnosis: clinical and laboratory.
Date of initial detection of animal health incident: 21 Jul 2002.
Estimated date of first infection: 9 Jul 2002.
No. of outbreaks: 8.
Location of the outbreaks: Erdeneburen (latitude 48*37*N, longitude
90*48*E), Khovd (Hovd) province, in the western part of the country.
Total number of animals in the outbreaks: 10 123 sheep and 1873 cattle.
Total number of cases: 66 head of cattle.
Total number of deaths: 1.
Source of agent / origin of infection: under investigation.
Mode of spread: free access to common pasture.
Control measures: quarantine and movement control inside the country; testing.
Further details will be published in the next issue of Weekly Disease
Information, available on line as from Fri, 26 Jul 2002 afternoon
(GMT).
--
